Form1.name: Will Swinton-Ginsberg
Form1.favorite_memory: On my first day at Awesome Inc, I was working on a webpage in the lab for about an hour and everyone was silent and glued to their computer. Then, all of a sudden, Brian grabbed a nerf gun and started shooting it indiscriminately at everyone in the office. Within about 30 seconds teams were established and an all out nerf gun battle had commenced. That moment summed up what I loved about Awesome Inc: a professional, hardworking environment that could turn into a nerf war at any moment.
Form1.how_ta_helped: Awesome Inc introduced me to a group of talented, hardworking people who dedicated themselves to helping others achieve their goals. These awesome individuals continue to be an inspiration for me to not only work my butt off to improve myself as a professional but also to understand that it's only worth it if I'm able to help others do the same.

Form1.name: David McGee
Form1.favorite_memory: Among the quality relationships and experiences that bloomed in my Awesome Inc days, I recall at MobileX Chicago there was a mixup in room keys. I found myself without a room late at night, but bumped into one of the keynote speakers who invited me to hang in his room. Rules 4, 17, 22, & 26 were invoked when no other room was found and Mr Keynote Kagan dared me to take the empty side of the bed next to the speaker from Google. This poor rich man awoke to the sight of a strange bearded fellow, napping to his right!
Form1.how_ta_helped: Team Alpha helped me to take small risks with high upsides.
